choices.text: You are given an integer m. Let M = 2^m - 1. You are also given a set of n integers denoted as the set T. The integers will be provided in base 2 as n binary strings of length m. A set of integers S is called "good" if the following hold.   If a ∈ S, then [Image].  If a, b ∈ S, then a ∧ b ∈ S                                                                                                                                                                                       ld;dr: Count the number of good sets S, modulo 10^9 + 7.
